{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Weak_Point",
  "title": "The Weak Point",
  "summary": "In a suite at the Plaxton Grand, the mechanic Orson Tighe grinds the second crystal for his lightsaber while his lover, the Jedi Jessalyn Valios, brings him a cold drink and gently urges patience. Haunted by flickering memories of his cold, unfaithful ex-wife Marina -- a ghostly presence stalking the closet of his mind -- and by guilt over the danger his Force-given gift poses, Orson confesses that he is afraid of how deeply he loves Jessalyn, and begs her to make him strong enough in the Force that he could never hurt her. Interwoven with dryly ironic excerpts from a maintenance manual he once wrote, the two work through his fear: Jessalyn admits she cannot make him stronger, that only he can, and that she trusts his love to keep him from the Dark Side. Orson lets some old support inside him give way, declares his love and faithfulness, and the apparition of Marina finally goes dark. Reaffirmed and at peace, Orson returns to the wheel and grinds the next facet of the gray-green gem -- and at last it is ready.",
